cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the use of vehicle-to-vehicle connectivity to improve emergency vehicle service, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a deep neural network-based approximate dynamic programming algorithm to efficiently compute optimal coordination instructions, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the coordination of connected vehicles to establish dynamic queue jumper lanes, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper proposes a solution to improve emergency vehicle service using technology, which falls under the domain of robotics. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a deep neural network-based algorithm, which falls under the domain of machine learning.
